<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="371" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[118,769,1606,1955]" lastBlockId="2.[844,1495,281,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis box="[156,301,1606,1630]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Observations</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[334,531,1606,1630]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Rotheca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudiflora">
<emphasis box="[334,531,1606,1630]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Rotheca nudiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the third species of the genus recognized for 
<collectingCountry box="[394,525,1639,1663]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and it is only one that is endemic. It can be easily recognized among other species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="STEANE &amp; MABBERLEY" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[147,235,1703,1727]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Rotheca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[147,235,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Rotheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its phenology: it is the only Malagasy species that flowers early in the season before the leaves develop (
<figureCitation box="[126,191,1768,1792]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[103,129,1764,1784]" captionTargetBox="[103,753,280,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[103,752,844,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. – Living plants of Rotheca nudiflora (Moldenke) Callm. &amp; Phillipson. A. Leafless stems, markedly asymmetrical flower buds; B. Corolla expanded abruptly in lower part with large anterior corolla lobe, non-resupinate flowers, basifixed anthers and green, non-fleshy fruits. [A: Ratovoson 1376 from Ampombiantambo, SW of Antsiranana; B: Phillipson &amp; al. 5942 from Ranobe forest, N of Toliara] [Photos: A: F. Ratovoson; B: P. B. Phillipson]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5710386" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5710386/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="MOLDENKE, H. N." box="[215,415,1768,1792]" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" pagination="406 - 448" refId="ref2531" refString="MOLDENKE, H. N. (1951). Notes on new and noteworthy plants. XII. Phytologia 3: 406 - 448." type="journal article" year="1951">MOLDENKE (1951)</bibRefCitation>
recognized two varieties within 
<taxonomicName box="[118,410,1801,1825]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Clerodendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudiflorum">
<emphasis box="[118,410,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Clerodendrum nudiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, segregating a single collection 
<emphasis box="[118,228,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Seyrig 91</emphasis>
, from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[420,558,1833,1857]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Clerodendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="nudiflorum" variety="puberulentum">
<emphasis box="[607,769,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">C. nudiflorum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[162,307,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">puberulentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of its puberulent rachis, peduncle, pedicels and calyx. Our critical review of all specimens available at G, K, MO, P and TAN has suggested that infraspecific taxa cannot be recognised in 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1427,281,305]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Rotheca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudiflora">
<emphasis box="[1236,1427,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Rotheca nudiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since there appears to be a variable degree of pubescence throughout its range in the dry forests and thickets of 
<collectingCountry box="[1356,1491,346,370]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. Besides, generally glabrous individuals often appear to have some pubescence in early stages of development.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="371" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="2.[843,1494,452,705]" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis box="[882,1087,452,476]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">Conservation status</emphasis>
. – With an extent of occurrence (EOO) of&gt; 
<quantity box="[896,1027,484,508]" metricMagnitude="8" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" unit="km" value="470000.0">470,000 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1027,1035,484,498]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">2</superScript>
, an area of occupancy (AOO) of 
<quantity box="[1403,1485,485,509]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.16" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" unit="km" value="216.0">216 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[1486,1494,484,498]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">2</superScript>
and&gt; 20 subpopulations, several encompassed in formally protected areas (Andohahela, Ankarana, Bemaraha, Beza Mahafaly, Namoroka), 
<taxonomicName box="[1029,1158,583,607]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Rotheca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="371" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudiflora">
<emphasis box="[1029,1158,583,607]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="371">R. nudiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assigned a preliminary status of Least Concern (LC) following the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (calculation following 
<bibRefCitation author="CALLMANDER, M. W. &amp; G. E &amp; SCHATZ, P. P. &amp; LOWRY II, M. O. &amp; LAIVAO, J. &amp; RAHARIMAMPIONONA, S. &amp; ANDRIAMBOLOLONERA, T." pageId="2" pageNumber="371" pagination="168 - 176" refId="ref2130" refString="CALLMANDER, M. W., G. E. SCHATZ, P. P. LOWRY II, M. O. LAIVAO, J. RAHARIMAMPIONONA, S. ANDRIAMBOLOLONERA, T. RAMINOSOA &amp; T. CONSIGLIO (2007). Application of IUCN Red List criteria and assessment of Priority Areas for Plant Conservation in Madagascar: rare and threatened Pandanaceae indicate new sites in need of protection. Oryx 42: 168 - 176." type="journal article" year="2007">CALLMANDER &amp; al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
